article.headline: Rhode Island 86, Stonehill 62
article.story: SOUTH KINGSTOWN, R.I. (AP) -- Kahiem Seawright had 20 points and 10 rebounds for Rhode Island in an 86-62 win over Stonehill on Friday night. Seawright made 8 of 10 shots, and his basket with 14:28 to play helped Rhode Island open up a 51-37 lead, the largest of the game to that point. Rhode Island led by as much as 30 later in the second half and outscored Stonehill 54-37 after half time. Will Daniels chipped in with 18 points and Joe Mbang had 17 for Rhode Island, 15 in the second half. Stonehill's Soap Toun hit four 3-pointers in the first half to help tie the game at 21-21. He had a game-high 26 points on 8-of-12 shooting from 3-point range. Nick Smith had 14 points for Stonehill. Rhode Island closed the first half with an 11-4 run to take a 32-25 lead into the break. Darrell Harris scored six points and Seawright added four of his 12 first-half points in that stretch. Harris finished with 10 points in 14 minutes of action.
